{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TmKptVZFDRzmP4Wt7ZGDxG","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive exploration report:\n\n## CLOCHE CODEBASE EXPLORATION REPORT\n\n### Project Overview\n\n**Cloche** is a system for grow-coding high-quality applications through containerized environments. It provides:\n- A workflow DSL for linking agentic and script-driven tasks\n- Containerized environments managed by a daemon\n- An orchestration loop for automated task assignment and completion\n- A web dashboard for project monitoring\n\n**Technology Stack:** Go, gRPC, SQLite, Docker, Protocol Buffers\n\n**Three core binaries from one module:**\n1. **cloche** (CLI) - Short-lived client communicating with daemon via gRPC\n2. **cloched** (Daemon) - Long-running process managing container lifecycle and orchestration\n3. **cloche-agent** (In-container) - Autonomous agent executing workflows inside containers\n\n---\n\n### ARCHITECTURE\n\n#### Hexagonal Architecture Pattern\nDomain logic is independent of infrastructure. Ports define interfaces, adapters implement them:\n\n```\ncmd/\n  cloche/           # CLI client\n  cloched/          # Daemon\n  cloche-agent/     # In-container entrypoint\ninternal/\n  domain/           # Core types (Workflow, Step, Result, Run)\n  ports/            # Interfaces (ContainerRuntime, RunStore, CaptureStore)\n  adapters/         # Implementations\n    docker/         # Docker runtime\n    sqlite/         # SQLite persistence\n    grpc/           # gRPC server\n    web/            # Web dashboard\n    agents/         # Agent adapters (Claude Code, etc)\n  host/             # Host workflow executor\n  engine/           # Workflow execution engine\n  dsl/              # DSL parser and lexer\n  config/           # Configuration management\napi/\n  proto/            # Protocol Buffer definitions\n```\n\n#### Project Layout\nCloche-specific files live in `.cloche/` at the project root:\n\n```\nmy-project/\n├── .cloche/\n│   ├── develop.cloche       # Container workflow definition\n│   ├── host.cloche          # Host orchestration workflow (runs on host)\n│   ├── Dockerfile           # Container image\n│   ├── config.toml          # Project configuration\n│   ├── prompts/             # Prompt templates for agent steps\n│   ├── scripts/             # Host-side scripts (claim-task.sh, etc)\n│   ├── overrides/           # Files copied on top of /workspace/ in container\n│   └── <run-id>/            # Runtime state (gitignored)\n├── src/                     # Existing project source (untouched)\n└── CLAUDE.md\n```\n\n---\n\n### CORE DOMAIN TYPES\n\n#### Run State Machine\nFile: `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n\n```go\ntype RunState string\n\nconst (\n    RunStatePending   RunState = \"pending\"\n    RunStateRunning   RunState = \"running\"\n    RunStateSucceeded RunState = \"succeeded\"\n    RunStateFailed    RunState = \"failed\"\n    RunStateCancelled RunState = \"cancelled\"\n)\n\ntype Run struct {\n    ID             string\n    WorkflowName   string\n    State          RunState\n    ActiveSteps    []string         // Currently executing steps\n    StepExecutions []*StepExecution // Complete execution history\n    StartedAt      time.Time\n    CompletedAt    time.Time\n    ProjectDir     string\n    ErrorMessage   string\n    ContainerID    string\n    BaseSHA        string           // Git HEAD at run start\n    ContainerKept  bool\n    Title          string           // One-line summary\n    IsHost         bool             // true for host workflows\n    ParentRunID    string           // ID of parent host run\n    TaskID         string           // optional task ID this run is for\n}\n\ntype StepExecution struct {\n    StepName    string\n    Result      string\n    StartedAt   time.Time\n    CompletedAt time.Time\n    Logs        string\n    GitRef      string\n}\n```\n\n#### Workflow Definition\nFile: `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`\n\n```go\ntype WorkflowLocation string\n\nconst (\n    LocationContainer WorkflowLocation = \"container\"\n    LocationHost      WorkflowLocation = \"host\"\n)\n\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string\n    Type    StepType         // agent, script, or workflow\n    Results []string         // result names this step can produce\n    Config  map[string]string\n}\n\ntype Wire struct {\n    From      string              // source step\n    Result    string              // which result triggers this wire\n    To        string              // target step (or \"done\"/\"abort\")\n    OutputMap []OutputMapping     // env vars extracted from step output\n}\n\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string\n    Location  WorkflowLocation\n    Steps     map[string]*Step\n    Wiring    []Wire              // step graph edges\n    Collects  []Collect           // fanin collection logic\n    EntryStep string\n    Config    map[string]string   // workflow-level config\n}\n```\n\n#### Task Management\nFile: `/workspace/internal/host/task.go`\n\n```go\ntype TaskStatus string\n\nconst (\n    TaskStatusOpen       TaskStatus = \"open\"\n    TaskStatusClosed     TaskStatus = \"closed\"\n    TaskStatusInProgress TaskStatus = \"in-progress\"\n)\n\ntype Task struct {\n    ID          string\n    Status      string\n    Title       string\n    Description string\n    Metadata    map[string]string\n}\n\nfunc (t Task) IsOpen() bool {\n    return t.Status == \"\" || TaskStatus(t.Status) == TaskStatusOpen\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### HOST WORKFLOW SYSTEM\n\n#### Three-Phase Orchestration\nFile: `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche`\n\n```\nworkflow \"list-tasks\" {\n  step ready-tasks {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  ready-tasks:success -> done\n  ready-tasks:fail    -> abort\n}\n\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  host { agent_command = \"claude\" }\n  \n  step claim-task { run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/claim-task.sh\" ... }\n  step prepare-prompt { run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\" ... }\n  step develop { workflow_name = \"develop\" ... }\n  step merge { run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/merge-to-main.sh\" ... }\n  step cleanup { run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/cleanup-run.sh\" ... }\n  \n  claim-task:success -> prepare-prompt\n  prepare-prompt:success -> develop\n  develop:success -> merge\n  merge:success -> cleanup\n  cleanup:success -> done\n}\n\nworkflow \"finalize\" {\n  step close-task { run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/close-task.sh\" ... }\n  close-task:success -> done\n}\n```\n\n#### Host Workflow Execution\nFile: `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`\n\n**Three-Phase Flow** (from `createPhaseLoop` in grpc/server.go):\n\n1. **list-tasks Phase**: Discovers available work via `list-tasks` workflow\n   - Calls `RunListTasksWorkflow()` which:\n     - Executes the `list-tasks` workflow\n     - Reads JSON output from `ready-tasks.sh`\n     - Returns parsed Task objects\n   - Result: `[]Task` with open tasks\n\n2. **main Phase**: Executes main workflow for each task (up to MaxConcurrent)\n   - Environment variables set by daemon:\n     - `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` - assigned task ID\n     - `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` - project directory\n     - `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` - host run ID\n   - Scripts can interact with run context:\n     - `cloche get <key>` - retrieve from context\n     - `cloche set <key> <value>` - store in context\n   - Workflow steps:\n     - **claim-task.sh**: Changes task status to \"in_progress\" via `bd update`\n     - **prepare-prompt.sh**: Fetches task details using `bd show`\n     - **develop**: Dispatches container workflow run\n     - **merge-to-main.sh**: Rebases feature branch onto main\n     - **cleanup-run.sh**: Removes worktree and feature branch\n\n3. **finalize Phase** (optional): Cleanup after main (success or failure)\n   - Environment variables from main result:\n     - `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` - child run ID from main phase\n     - `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` - \"succeeded\" or \"failed\"\n   - Workflow step:\n     - **close-task.sh**: Closes task if main succeeded, otherwise leaves open for retry\n\n#### Host Executor\nFile: `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`\n\n```go\ntype Executor struct {\n    ProjectDir    string\n    MainDir       string         // main branch worktree for script execution\n    Dispatcher    RunDispatcher  // dispatches container runs\n    Store         ports.RunStore // persists run state\n    OutputDir     string         // .cloche/<run-id>/output/\n    Wires         []domain.Wire  // for output mappings\n    HostRunID     string         // parent host run ID\n    AgentCommands []string       // fallback agent command chain\n    AgentArgs     []string       // explicit agent args\n    TaskID        string         // daemon-assigned task ID\n    ExtraEnv      []string       // KEY=VALUE env vars for all steps\n}\n\nfunc (e *Executor) Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error)\n    // Dispatches to: executeScript, executeWorkflow, or executeAgent\n\nfunc (e *Executor) executeScript(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error)\n    // Runs shell command with CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR, CLOCHE_RUN_ID, CLOCHE_TASK_ID\n\nfunc (e *Executor) executeWorkflow(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error)\n    // Dispatches container run, waits for completion, polls every 2s\n\nfunc (e *Executor) executeAgent(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error)\n    // Runs agent (Claude Code) on host\n```\n\n#### Orchestration Loop\nFile: `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`\n\n```go\ntype Loop struct {\n    config     LoopConfig\n    listTasks  ListTasksFunc  // phase 1\n    mainFn     MainFunc       // phase 2\n    finalizeFn FinalizeFunc   // phase 3 (optional)\n    store      ports.RunStore\n    stopCh     chan struct{}\n    dedup      map[string]time.Time // task ID -> last assignment time\n    taskRuns   map[string]TaskAssignment // task ID -> (RunID, AssignedAt)\n    lastTasks  []Task         // cached task list\n}\n\nfunc (l *Loop) GetTaskSnapshot() []TaskStateEntry {\n    // Returns current task pipeline state:\n    // - Task details\n    // - Whether assigned (within dedup window)\n    // - Run ID if known\n}\n\nfunc (l *Loop) runPhased() {\n    // Main loop:\n    // 1. For each open, non-deduped task (up to MaxConcurrent):\n    //    - Call listTasksFn() to discover work\n    //    - Call mainFn() for each task (in goroutine)\n    //    - Call finalizeFn() after main completes (success/failure)\n    // 2. Stagger launches by StaggerDelay\n    // 3. Poll with capacityPollInterval when idle\n}\n```\n\n**Configuration:**\n```go\ntype LoopConfig struct {\n    ProjectDir    string\n    MaxConcurrent int\n    StaggerDelay  time.Duration  // delay between launches\n    DedupTimeout  time.Duration  // suppress task reassignment (default: 5m)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### TASK MANAGEMENT SYSTEM\n\n#### Task Provider Interface\nFile: `/workspace/internal/host/task.go`\n\n```go\ntype TaskAssigner interface {\n    ListTasks(ctx context.Context, projectDir string) ([]Task, error)\n}\n\ntype ScriptTaskAssigner struct {\n    Command string // e.g., \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\n}\n\nfunc (s *ScriptTaskAssigner) ListTasks(ctx context.Context, projectDir string) ([]Task, error) {\n    // Runs shell command, parses JSON array output\n}\n\nfunc ParseTasksJSONL(data string) ([]Task, error)\n    // Parses JSONL format (one JSON object per line)\n```\n\n#### Task Lifecycle Scripts\nLocated in `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/`:\n\n1. **ready-tasks.sh** - List available tasks\n   - Runs: `bd list -s open --json`\n   - Output: JSONL format\n   - Converts JSON array to JSONL (one object per line)\n\n2. **claim-task.sh** - Claim a task for processing\n   - Uses: `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var\n   - Runs: `bd update $CLOCHE_TASK_ID -s in_progress`\n   - Sets task status to \"in_progress\"\n\n3. **prepare-prompt.sh** - Build task prompt\n   - Uses: `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var\n   - Runs: `bd show $CLOCHE_TASK_ID --json`\n   - Extracts title and description\n   - Outputs prompt that will be passed to child workflow\n\n4. **merge-to-main.sh** - Merge child run results\n   - Uses: `cloche get child_run_id`\n   - Rebases feature branch onto main\n   - Handles rebase conflicts (prefers main)\n   - Deletes feature branch after successful merge\n\n5. **cleanup-run.sh** - Remove worktree and branch\n   - Uses: `cloche get child_run_id`\n   - Removes git worktree\n   - Prunes stale worktree bookkeeping\n   - Deletes feature branch if still present\n\n6. **close-task.sh** - Close completed task\n   - Uses: `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` env vars\n   - If outcome == \"succeeded\": `bd close $CLOCHE_TASK_ID`\n   - Otherwise: leaves task open for retry\n\n#### Task State Tracking\nFile: `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`\n\n```go\ntype TaskAssignment struct {\n    AssignedAt time.Time\n    RunID      string // run ID handling this task (set after main completes)\n}\n\ntype TaskStateEntry struct {\n    Task       Task\n    Assigned   bool               // within dedup window\n    AssignedAt time.Time\n    RunID      string             // empty if not yet run\n}\n\nfunc (l *Loop) GetTaskSnapshot() []TaskStateEntry {\n    // Combines:\n    // - lastTasks (from latest list-tasks call)\n    // - dedup map (task assignment times)\n    // - taskRuns map (run IDs for each task)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### PROJECT VIEW IMPLEMENTATION\n\n#### Project View Command\nFile: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/project.go`\n\n```go\nfunc cmdProject(args []string) {\n    // Flags: --name <project-name>\n    // Queries daemon gRPC: GetProjectInfo()\n    \n    // Displays:\n    // - Project name and directory\n    // - Config: active, concurrency, stagger_seconds, evolution\n    // - Loop status: running/stopped\n    // - Active runs (with workflow, state, type)\n    // - Container workflows (names)\n    // - Host workflows (names)\n}\n```\n\n#### GetProjectInfo RPC\nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 1007-1110)\n\n```go\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) GetProjectInfo(ctx context.Context, req *pb.GetProjectInfoRequest) (*pb.GetProjectInfoResponse, error) {\n    // Input: ProjectDir OR Name\n    // Resolves name to directory if needed\n    \n    // Collects:\n    // - Project label (from projectLabels map)\n    // - Config from .cloche/config.toml\n    // - Loop state (running, stopped, or not created)\n    // - Active runs (pending/running for this project)\n    // - Container workflows (*.cloche except host.cloche)\n    // - Host workflows (from host.cloche)\n    \n    // Returns:\n    type GetProjectInfoResponse {\n        ProjectDir:         string\n        Name:               string\n        Active:             bool\n        Concurrency:        int32\n        StaggerSeconds:     float64\n        DedupSeconds:       float64\n        EvolutionEnabled:   bool\n        LoopRunning:        bool\n        ActiveRuns:         []*RunSummary\n        ContainerWorkflows: []string\n        HostWorkflows:      []string\n    }\n    \n    type RunSummary {\n        RunId:        string\n        WorkflowName: string\n        State:        string\n        StartedAt:    string\n        Title:        string\n        IsHost:       bool\n        ContainerId:  string\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### Web Dashboard Project Views\nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\n**handleProjectOverview** (lines 195-248)\n- Shows all projects with health cards\n- Displays recent run history dots\n- Shows active run count\n- Uses CalculateHealth() for status indicators\n\n**handleProjectDetail** (lines 1206-1240)\n- Shows recent 10 runs with status dots\n- Displays container count\n- Serves HTML page at `/projects/{name}`\n\n**handleAPIProjectInfo** (lines 1242-1333)\n- Returns JSON with:\n  - Docker image from Dockerfile\n  - Version number from .cloche/version\n  - Prompt files with git history (commits, dates, diffs)\n\n**handleAPITasks** (lines 1587-1606)\n- Returns task list from `taskProvider.GetLoopTasks(dir)`\n- Calls `handler.taskProvider.GetLoopTasks(projectDir)`\n- TaskProvider implemented by gRPC server\n\n**handleAPIWorkflows** (lines 1366+)\n- Discovers .cloche/*.cloche files\n- Parses workflows using DSL\n- Returns JSON with steps, wiring, config for each workflow\n\n#### Web Templates\nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n\n**Panels:**\n1. **Project Info** - Docker image, version, prompt file history\n2. **Tasks** - Table with ID, title, status (open/in-progress/closed), assigned flag, run link\n3. **Workflows** - Tabs for container/host workflows, DAG visualization\n\n**Task Table Rendering** (lines 499-532):\n```javascript\nfunction loadTasks() {\n    fetch('/api/projects/{name}/tasks')\n        .then(r => r.json())\n        .then(tasks => {\n            // Renders table with columns:\n            // - Task ID\n            // - Title\n            // - Status (badge: open=running, closed=succeeded, in-progress=pending)\n            // - Assigned (Yes/No)\n            // - Run (linked to run detail page)\n        })\n}\nloadTasks();\nsetInterval(loadTasks, 5000);  // Refresh every 5 seconds\n```\n\n---\n\n### CONFIGURATION SYSTEM\n\n#### Project Configuration\nFile: `/workspace/internal/config/config.go`\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Active        bool                `toml:\"active\"`\n    Daemon        DaemonConfig\n    Evolution     EvolutionConfig\n    Orchestration OrchestrationConfig\n}\n\ntype OrchestrationConfig struct {\n    Concurrency      int     `toml:\"concurrency\"`         // default: 1\n    StaggerSeconds   float64 `toml:\"stagger_seconds\"`     // default: 1.0\n    ListTasksCommand string  `toml:\"list_tasks_command\"`  // shell command\n    DedupSeconds     float64 `toml:\"dedup_seconds\"`       // default: 300\n}\n\ntype EvolutionConfig struct {\n    Enabled          bool   `toml:\"enabled\"`\n    DebounceSeconds  int    `toml:\"debounce_seconds\"`\n    MinConfidence    string `toml:\"min_confidence\"`\n    MaxPromptBullets int    `toml:\"max_prompt_bullets\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Config File Location:**\n- Per-project: `<projectDir>/.cloche/config.toml`\n- Global daemon: `~/.config/cloche/config`\n\n---\n\n### WORKFLOW DSL\n\n#### DSL Parser\nFile: `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`\n\n```go\nfunc ParseAllForHost(input string) (map[string]*domain.Workflow, error)\n    // Parses host.cloche which can have multiple workflows\n    // Returns: map[workflowName]*domain.Workflow\n\nfunc ParseForContainer(input string) (*domain.Workflow, error)\n    // Parses container workflow file (*.cloche)\n    // Returns: single *domain.Workflow\n```\n\n#### Step Types\n```go\ntype StepType string\n\nconst (\n    StepTypeAgent    StepType = \"agent\"      // runs agent (Claude Code)\n    StepTypeScript   StepType = \"script\"     // runs shell command\n    StepTypeWorkflow StepType = \"workflow\"   // dispatches container run\n)\n```\n\n#### Result Markers\nSteps can use markers to override exit code behavior:\n- Format: `[CLOCHE_RESULT: <result>]` in output\n- Default: \"success\" on exit 0, \"fail\" on non-zero\n\n---\n\n### EXECUTION ENGINE\n\n#### Workflow Execution\nFile: `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`\n\n```go\ntype Engine struct {\n    executor       StepExecutor      // executes individual steps\n    status         StatusHandler     // receives progress events\n    maxSteps       int               // max steps per run (default: 1000)\n    defaultTimeout time.Duration     // default step timeout (default: 30m)\n}\n\ntype StepExecutor interface {\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error)\n}\n\ntype StatusHandler interface {\n    OnStepStart(run *domain.Run, step *domain.Step)\n    OnStepComplete(run *domain.Run, step *domain.Step, result string)\n    OnRunComplete(run *domain.Run)\n}\n\nfunc (e *Engine) Run(ctx context.Context, wf *domain.Workflow) (*domain.Run, error)\n    // Executes workflow graph starting from EntryStep\n    // Handles wiring, result routing, fanout/fanin\n    // Manages step timeouts\n```\n\n---\n\n### ACTIVE WORKERS AND RUNS TRACKING\n\n#### Run Persistence\nFile: `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n    ID          string             // unique run ID (generated)\n    State       RunState           // pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled\n    ActiveSteps []string           // steps currently executing\n    ParentRunID string             // for child runs (non-empty if launched by host workflow)\n    IsHost      bool               // true if this is a host workflow run\n    TaskID      string             // optional task ID this run is for\n}\n\nfunc TaskAggregateStatus(runs []*Run) RunState {\n    // Computes aggregate status for runs handling same task\n    // Active statuses (running, pending) outweigh terminal ones\n    // Returns state of most recent run if all terminal\n}\n```\n\n#### Run Store Interface\nFile: `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`\n\n```go\ntype RunStore interface {\n    CreateRun(ctx context.Context, run *Run) error\n    UpdateRun(ctx context.Context, run *Run) error\n    GetRun(ctx context.Context, runID string) (*Run, error)\n    ListRuns(ctx context.Context) ([]*Run, error)\n    ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*Run, error)\n    ListRunsByTask(ctx context.Context, taskID string) ([]*Run, error)\n    FailStaleRuns(ctx context.Context) (int, error)\n}\n```\n\n#### Active Run Tracking in Loop\nFile: `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` (lines 485-498)\n\n```go\nfunc (l *Loop) countActiveHostRuns() int {\n    runs, err := l.store.ListRunsByProject(ctx, l.config.ProjectDir, time.Time{})\n    count := 0\n    for _, r := range runs {\n        if r.IsHost && (r.State == domain.RunStatePending || r.State == domain.RunStateRunning) {\n            count++\n        }\n    }\n    return count\n}\n\n// Loop uses this to enforce MaxConcurrent limit:\n// - Counts active host runs at start of each iteration\n// - Only launches new runs if active < MaxConcurrent\n// - Waits for a run to complete before filling slot\n```\n\n---\n\n### KEY FILES SUMMARY\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche` | Host workflow definitions (list-tasks, main, finalize) |\n| `/workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche` | Container workflow definition |\n| `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/*.sh` | Host-side scripts for task lifecycle |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | Run state machine and execution tracking |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` | Workflow structure, steps, wiring |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/task.go` | Task types and task assigner interface |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` | Orchestration loop (three-phase or legacy) |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` | Host workflow step executor |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` | Host workflow runner, RunListTasksWorkflow |\n| `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` | Workflow execution engine |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | gRPC service, EnableLoop, GetProjectInfo, GetLoopTasks |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | Web dashboard handlers |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` | Project view HTML with task table |\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloche/project.go` | Project info CLI command |\n| `/workspace/internal/config/config.go` | Configuration loading (project and daemon) |\n\n---\n\n### WORKFLOW EXECUTION FLOW\n\n#### Container Workflow (develop.cloche)\n```\n1. User: cloche run develop --prompt \"...\"\n2. CLI: Sends RunWorkflow(workflow=\"develop\", projectDir=cwd)\n3. Daemon: Creates run, pulls/starts container, mounts project\n4. Container Agent: Parses workflow, walks graph, executes steps\n5. Steps: \n   - implement (agent step)\n   - test (script step)\n   - fix (agent step, with retry up to max_attempts)\n   - update-docs (agent step)\n6. Result: Commits to new branch cloche/{runID}\n7. Artifact: Branch contains all changes from workflow execution\n```\n\n#### Host Workflow Three-Phase (host.cloche)\n```\nPhase 1: list-tasks\n  cloche loop start\n  ├─ Runs list-tasks workflow\n  ├─ Execute: ready-tasks.sh → bd list\n  └─ Result: []Task (open tasks)\n\nPhase 2: main (for each open task, up to MaxConcurrent)\n  ├─ CLOCHE_TASK_ID=<task-id> set by daemon\n  ├─ claim-task.sh → bd update (set in_progress)\n  ├─ prepare-prompt.sh → bd show (fetch task details)\n  ├─ develop (dispatch container run, wait for result)\n  ├─ merge-to-main.sh (rebase branch onto main)\n  └─ cleanup-run.sh (remove worktree)\n  \n  Container Run Executes:\n    └─ develop workflow\n       ├─ implement (Claude Code)\n       ├─ test (bash: go test)\n       ├─ fix (Claude Code, retry on failure)\n       └─ update-docs (Claude Code)\n       \n  Result: cloche/{runID} branch merged to main\n\nPhase 3: finalize (after each main completes)\n  ├─ CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID=<child-run-id>\n  ├─ CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME=<succeeded|failed>\n  └─ close-task.sh → bd close (if succeeded)\n```\n\n---\n\n### TASK PIPELINE STATE\n\nThe orchestration loop maintains task state via three mechanisms:\n\n1. **lastTasks**: Most recently fetched tasks from list-tasks\n2. **dedup**: Task ID → assignment time (prevents rapid reassignment for DedupTimeout)\n3. **taskRuns**: Task ID → (RunID, AssignedAt) for tracking which run handled each task\n\n**GetTaskSnapshot()** combines these into TaskStateEntry for web dashboard:\n- Task details (ID, title, status, description, metadata)\n- Assigned: bool (true if within dedup window)\n- AssignedAt: time (when deduped or run started)\n- RunID: string (non-empty if main has completed for this task)\n\n---\n\nThis comprehensive exploration captures the full architecture of Cloche's task/bead system, project view implementation, and workflow execution mechanisms. All the key interfaces, data structures, and orchestration patterns are documented with file paths and line numbers for reference."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ae71f7945c9023306 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 85708\ntool_uses: 59\nduration_ms: 160476</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09a1d66f-c28d-47e8-9d4e-ccb126644895","uuid":"4c1bdb1f-55d5-4b01-876d-74c4f7ebde93","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly to understand:\n\n1. The Project view implementation - how tasks are currently displayed. Look for any TUI/view code related to \"project\" views.\n2. The host workflow system - how host.cloche workflows are defined and executed.\n3. The task/bead system - how tasks are claimed, assigned, and managed.\n4. The worker/run system - how active workers and runs are tracked.\n5. Look at `.cloche/host.cloche` for existing workflow definitions.\n6. Look at `.cloche/scripts/` for existing scripts.\n7. Look at the domain types for Run, Task, Worker status.\n8. Look at how `list-tasks` workflow works.\n\nSearch for files matching patterns like:\n- `**/*project*`\n- `**/*task*`\n- `**/*view*`\n- `**/*host*`\n- `**/*worker*`\n- `**/*release*`\n- `**/*bead*`\n- `.cloche/**`\n- `internal/domain/**`\n- `internal/host/**`\n- `cmd/**`\n\nBe very thorough - I need to understand the full picture before implementing.","agentId":"ae71f7945c9023306","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive exploration report:\n\n## CLOCHE CODEBASE EXPLORATION REPORT\n\n### Project Overview\n\n**Cloche** is a system for grow-coding high-quality applications through containerized environments. It provides:\n- A workflow DSL for linking agentic and script-driven tasks\n- Containerized environments managed by a daemon\n- An orchestration loop for automated task assignment and completion\n- A web dashboard for project monitoring\n\n**Technology Stack:** Go, gRPC, SQLite, Docker, Protocol Buffers\n\n**Three core binaries from one module:**\n1. **cloche** (CLI) - Short-lived client communicating with daemon via gRPC\n2. **cloched** (Daemon) - Long-running process managing container lifecycle and orchestration\n3. **cloche-agent** (In-container) - Autonomous agent executing workflows inside containers\n\n---\n\n### ARCHITECTURE\n\n#### Hexagonal Architecture Pattern\nDomain logic is independent of infrastructure. Ports define interfaces, adapters implement them:\n\n```\ncmd/\n  cloche/           # CLI client\n  cloched/          # Daemon\n  cloche-agent/     # In-container entrypoint\ninternal/\n  domain/           # Core types (Workflow, Step, Result, Run)\n  ports/            # Interfaces (ContainerRuntime, RunStore, CaptureStore)\n  adapters/         # Implementations\n    docker/         # Docker runtime\n    sqlite/         # SQLite persistence\n    grpc/           # gRPC server\n    web/            # Web dashboard\n    agents/         # Agent adapters (Claude Code, etc)\n  host/             # Host workflow executor\n  engine/           # Workflow execution engine\n  dsl/              # DSL parser and lexer\n  config/           # Configuration management\napi/\n  proto/            # Protocol Buffer definitions\n```\n\n#### Project Layout\nCloche-specific files live in `.cloche/` at the project root:\n\n```\nmy-project/\n├── .cloche/\n│   ├── develop.cloche       # Container workflow definition\n│   ├── host.cloche          # Host orchestration workflow (runs on host)\n│   ├── Dockerfile           # Container image\n│   ├── config.toml          # Project configuration\n│   ├── prompts/             # Prompt templates for agent steps\n│   ├── scripts/             # Host-side scripts (claim-task.sh, etc)\n│   ├── overrides/           # Files copied on top of /workspace/ in container\n│   └── <run-id>/            # Runtime state (gitignored)\n├── src/                     # Existing project source (untouched)\n└── CLAUDE.md\n```\n\n---\n\n### CORE DOMAIN TYPES\n\n#### Run State Machine\nFile: `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n\n```go\ntype RunState string\n\nconst (\n    RunStatePending   RunState = \"pending\"\n    RunStateRunning   RunState = \"running\"\n    RunStateSucceeded RunState = \"succeeded\"\n    RunStateFailed    RunState = \"failed\"\n    RunStateCancelled RunState = \"cancelled\"\n)\n\ntype Run struct {\n    ID             string\n    WorkflowName   string\n    State          RunState\n    ActiveSteps    []string         // Currently executing steps\n    StepExecutions []*StepExecution // Complete execution history\n    StartedAt      time.Time\n    CompletedAt    time.Time\n    ProjectDir     string\n    ErrorMessage   string\n    ContainerID    string\n    BaseSHA        string           // Git HEAD at run start\n    ContainerKept  bool\n    Title          string           // One-line summary\n    IsHost         bool             // true for host workflows\n    ParentRunID    string           // ID of parent host run\n    TaskID         string           // optional task ID this run is for\n}\n\ntype StepExecution struct {\n    StepName    string\n    Result      string\n    StartedAt   time.Time\n    CompletedAt time.Time\n    Logs        string\n    GitRef      string\n}\n```\n\n#### Workflow Definition\nFile: `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`\n\n```go\ntype WorkflowLocation string\n\nconst (\n    LocationContainer WorkflowLocation = \"container\"\n    LocationHost      WorkflowLocation = \"host\"\n)\n\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string\n    Type    StepType         // agent, script, or workflow\n    Results []string         // result names this step can produce\n    Config  map[string]string\n}\n\ntype Wire struct {\n    From      string              // source step\n    Result    string              // which result triggers this wire\n    To        string              // target step (or \"done\"/\"abort\")\n    OutputMap []OutputMapping     // env vars extracted from step output\n}\n\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string\n    Location  WorkflowLocation\n    Steps     map[string]*Step\n    Wiring    []Wire              // step graph edges\n    Collects  []Collect           // fanin collection logic\n    EntryStep string\n    Config    map[string]string   // workflow-level config\n}\n```\n\n#### Task Management\nFile: `/workspace/internal/host/task.go`\n\n```go\ntype TaskStatus string\n\nconst (\n    TaskStatusOpen       TaskStatus = \"open\"\n    TaskStatusClosed     TaskStatus = \"closed\"\n    TaskStatusInProgress TaskStatus = \"in-progress\"\n)\n\ntype Task struct {\n    ID          string\n    Status      string\n    Title       string\n    Description string\n    Metadata    map[string]string\n}\n\nfunc (t Task) IsOpen() bool {\n    return t.Status == \"\" || TaskStatus(t.Status) == TaskStatusOpen\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### HOST WORKFLOW SYSTEM\n\n#### Three-Phase Orchestration\nFile: `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche`\n\n```\nworkflow \"list-tasks\" {\n  step ready-tasks {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  ready-tasks:success -> done\n  ready-tasks:fail    -> abort\n}\n\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  host { agent_command = \"claude\" }\n  \n  step claim-task { run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/claim-task.sh\" ... }\n  step prepare-prompt { run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\" ... }\n  step develop { workflow_name = \"develop\" ... }\n  step merge { run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/merge-to-main.sh\" ... }\n  step cleanup { run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/cleanup-run.sh\" ... }\n  \n  claim-task:success -> prepare-prompt\n  prepare-prompt:success -> develop\n  develop:success -> merge\n  merge:success -> cleanup\n  cleanup:success -> done\n}\n\nworkflow \"finalize\" {\n  step close-task { run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/close-task.sh\" ... }\n  close-task:success -> done\n}\n```\n\n#### Host Workflow Execution\nFile: `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`\n\n**Three-Phase Flow** (from `createPhaseLoop` in grpc/server.go):\n\n1. **list-tasks Phase**: Discovers available work via `list-tasks` workflow\n   - Calls `RunListTasksWorkflow()` which:\n     - Executes the `list-tasks` workflow\n     - Reads JSON output from `ready-tasks.sh`\n     - Returns parsed Task objects\n   - Result: `[]Task` with open tasks\n\n2. **main Phase**: Executes main workflow for each task (up to MaxConcurrent)\n   - Environment variables set by daemon:\n     - `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` - assigned task ID\n     - `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` - project directory\n     - `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` - host run ID\n   - Scripts can interact with run context:\n     - `cloche get <key>` - retrieve from context\n     - `cloche set <key> <value>` - store in context\n   - Workflow steps:\n     - **claim-task.sh**: Changes task status to \"in_progress\" via `bd update`\n     - **prepare-prompt.sh**: Fetches task details using `bd show`\n     - **develop**: Dispatches container workflow run\n     - **merge-to-main.sh**: Rebases feature branch onto main\n     - **cleanup-run.sh**: Removes worktree and feature branch\n\n3. **finalize Phase** (optional): Cleanup after main (success or failure)\n   - Environment variables from main result:\n     - `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` - child run ID from main phase\n     - `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` - \"succeeded\" or \"failed\"\n   - Workflow step:\n     - **close-task.sh**: Closes task if main succeeded, otherwise leaves open for retry\n\n#### Host Executor\nFile: `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`\n\n```go\ntype Executor struct {\n    ProjectDir    string\n    MainDir       string         // main branch worktree for script execution\n    Dispatcher    RunDispatcher  // dispatches container runs\n    Store         ports.RunStore // persists run state\n    OutputDir     string         // .cloche/<run-id>/output/\n    Wires         []domain.Wire  // for output mappings\n    HostRunID     string         // parent host run ID\n    AgentCommands []string       // fallback agent command chain\n    AgentArgs     []string       // explicit agent args\n    TaskID        string         // daemon-assigned task ID\n    ExtraEnv      []string       // KEY=VALUE env vars for all steps\n}\n\nfunc (e *Executor) Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error)\n    // Dispatches to: executeScript, executeWorkflow, or executeAgent\n\nfunc (e *Executor) executeScript(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error)\n    // Runs shell command with CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR, CLOCHE_RUN_ID, CLOCHE_TASK_ID\n\nfunc (e *Executor) executeWorkflow(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error)\n    // Dispatches container run, waits for completion, polls every 2s\n\nfunc (e *Executor) executeAgent(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error)\n    // Runs agent (Claude Code) on host\n```\n\n#### Orchestration Loop\nFile: `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`\n\n```go\ntype Loop struct {\n    config     LoopConfig\n    listTasks  ListTasksFunc  // phase 1\n    mainFn     MainFunc       // phase 2\n    finalizeFn FinalizeFunc   // phase 3 (optional)\n    store      ports.RunStore\n    stopCh     chan struct{}\n    dedup      map[string]time.Time // task ID -> last assignment time\n    taskRuns   map[string]TaskAssignment // task ID -> (RunID, AssignedAt)\n    lastTasks  []Task         // cached task list\n}\n\nfunc (l *Loop) GetTaskSnapshot() []TaskStateEntry {\n    // Returns current task pipeline state:\n    // - Task details\n    // - Whether assigned (within dedup window)\n    // - Run ID if known\n}\n\nfunc (l *Loop) runPhased() {\n    // Main loop:\n    // 1. For each open, non-deduped task (up to MaxConcurrent):\n    //    - Call listTasksFn() to discover work\n    //    - Call mainFn() for each task (in goroutine)\n    //    - Call finalizeFn() after main completes (success/failure)\n    // 2. Stagger launches by StaggerDelay\n    // 3. Poll with capacityPollInterval when idle\n}\n```\n\n**Configuration:**\n```go\ntype LoopConfig struct {\n    ProjectDir    string\n    MaxConcurrent int\n    StaggerDelay  time.Duration  // delay between launches\n    DedupTimeout  time.Duration  // suppress task reassignment (default: 5m)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### TASK MANAGEMENT SYSTEM\n\n#### Task Provider Interface\nFile: `/workspace/internal/host/task.go`\n\n```go\ntype TaskAssigner interface {\n    ListTasks(ctx context.Context, projectDir string) ([]Task, error)\n}\n\ntype ScriptTaskAssigner struct {\n    Command string // e.g., \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\n}\n\nfunc (s *ScriptTaskAssigner) ListTasks(ctx context.Context, projectDir string) ([]Task, error) {\n    // Runs shell command, parses JSON array output\n}\n\nfunc ParseTasksJSONL(data string) ([]Task, error)\n    // Parses JSONL format (one JSON object per line)\n```\n\n#### Task Lifecycle Scripts\nLocated in `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/`:\n\n1. **ready-tasks.sh** - List available tasks\n   - Runs: `bd list -s open --json`\n   - Output: JSONL format\n   - Converts JSON array to JSONL (one object per line)\n\n2. **claim-task.sh** - Claim a task for processing\n   - Uses: `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var\n   - Runs: `bd update $CLOCHE_TASK_ID -s in_progress`\n   - Sets task status to \"in_progress\"\n\n3. **prepare-prompt.sh** - Build task prompt\n   - Uses: `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var\n   - Runs: `bd show $CLOCHE_TASK_ID --json`\n   - Extracts title and description\n   - Outputs prompt that will be passed to child workflow\n\n4. **merge-to-main.sh** - Merge child run results\n   - Uses: `cloche get child_run_id`\n   - Rebases feature branch onto main\n   - Handles rebase conflicts (prefers main)\n   - Deletes feature branch after successful merge\n\n5. **cleanup-run.sh** - Remove worktree and branch\n   - Uses: `cloche get child_run_id`\n   - Removes git worktree\n   - Prunes stale worktree bookkeeping\n   - Deletes feature branch if still present\n\n6. **close-task.sh** - Close completed task\n   - Uses: `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` env vars\n   - If outcome == \"succeeded\": `bd close $CLOCHE_TASK_ID`\n   - Otherwise: leaves task open for retry\n\n#### Task State Tracking\nFile: `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`\n\n```go\ntype TaskAssignment struct {\n    AssignedAt time.Time\n    RunID      string // run ID handling this task (set after main completes)\n}\n\ntype TaskStateEntry struct {\n    Task       Task\n    Assigned   bool               // within dedup window\n    AssignedAt time.Time\n    RunID      string             // empty if not yet run\n}\n\nfunc (l *Loop) GetTaskSnapshot() []TaskStateEntry {\n    // Combines:\n    // - lastTasks (from latest list-tasks call)\n    // - dedup map (task assignment times)\n    // - taskRuns map (run IDs for each task)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### PROJECT VIEW IMPLEMENTATION\n\n#### Project View Command\nFile: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/project.go`\n\n```go\nfunc cmdProject(args []string) {\n    // Flags: --name <project-name>\n    // Queries daemon gRPC: GetProjectInfo()\n    \n    // Displays:\n    // - Project name and directory\n    // - Config: active, concurrency, stagger_seconds, evolution\n    // - Loop status: running/stopped\n    // - Active runs (with workflow, state, type)\n    // - Container workflows (names)\n    // - Host workflows (names)\n}\n```\n\n#### GetProjectInfo RPC\nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 1007-1110)\n\n```go\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) GetProjectInfo(ctx context.Context, req *pb.GetProjectInfoRequest) (*pb.GetProjectInfoResponse, error) {\n    // Input: ProjectDir OR Name\n    // Resolves name to directory if needed\n    \n    // Collects:\n    // - Project label (from projectLabels map)\n    // - Config from .cloche/config.toml\n    // - Loop state (running, stopped, or not created)\n    // - Active runs (pending/running for this project)\n    // - Container workflows (*.cloche except host.cloche)\n    // - Host workflows (from host.cloche)\n    \n    // Returns:\n    type GetProjectInfoResponse {\n        ProjectDir:         string\n        Name:               string\n        Active:             bool\n        Concurrency:        int32\n        StaggerSeconds:     float64\n        DedupSeconds:       float64\n        EvolutionEnabled:   bool\n        LoopRunning:        bool\n        ActiveRuns:         []*RunSummary\n        ContainerWorkflows: []string\n        HostWorkflows:      []string\n    }\n    \n    type RunSummary {\n        RunId:        string\n        WorkflowName: string\n        State:        string\n        StartedAt:    string\n        Title:        string\n        IsHost:       bool\n        ContainerId:  string\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### Web Dashboard Project Views\nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\n**handleProjectOverview** (lines 195-248)\n- Shows all projects with health cards\n- Displays recent run history dots\n- Shows active run count\n- Uses CalculateHealth() for status indicators\n\n**handleProjectDetail** (lines 1206-1240)\n- Shows recent 10 runs with status dots\n- Displays container count\n- Serves HTML page at `/projects/{name}`\n\n**handleAPIProjectInfo** (lines 1242-1333)\n- Returns JSON with:\n  - Docker image from Dockerfile\n  - Version number from .cloche/version\n  - Prompt files with git history (commits, dates, diffs)\n\n**handleAPITasks** (lines 1587-1606)\n- Returns task list from `taskProvider.GetLoopTasks(dir)`\n- Calls `handler.taskProvider.GetLoopTasks(projectDir)`\n- TaskProvider implemented by gRPC server\n\n**handleAPIWorkflows** (lines 1366+)\n- Discovers .cloche/*.cloche files\n- Parses workflows using DSL\n- Returns JSON with steps, wiring, config for each workflow\n\n#### Web Templates\nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n\n**Panels:**\n1. **Project Info** - Docker image, version, prompt file history\n2. **Tasks** - Table with ID, title, status (open/in-progress/closed), assigned flag, run link\n3. **Workflows** - Tabs for container/host workflows, DAG visualization\n\n**Task Table Rendering** (lines 499-532):\n```javascript\nfunction loadTasks() {\n    fetch('/api/projects/{name}/tasks')\n        .then(r => r.json())\n        .then(tasks => {\n            // Renders table with columns:\n            // - Task ID\n            // - Title\n            // - Status (badge: open=running, closed=succeeded, in-progress=pending)\n            // - Assigned (Yes/No)\n            // - Run (linked to run detail page)\n        })\n}\nloadTasks();\nsetInterval(loadTasks, 5000);  // Refresh every 5 seconds\n```\n\n---\n\n### CONFIGURATION SYSTEM\n\n#### Project Configuration\nFile: `/workspace/internal/config/config.go`\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Active        bool                `toml:\"active\"`\n    Daemon        DaemonConfig\n    Evolution     EvolutionConfig\n    Orchestration OrchestrationConfig\n}\n\ntype OrchestrationConfig struct {\n    Concurrency      int     `toml:\"concurrency\"`         // default: 1\n    StaggerSeconds   float64 `toml:\"stagger_seconds\"`     // default: 1.0\n    ListTasksCommand string  `toml:\"list_tasks_command\"`  // shell command\n    DedupSeconds     float64 `toml:\"dedup_seconds\"`       // default: 300\n}\n\ntype EvolutionConfig struct {\n    Enabled          bool   `toml:\"enabled\"`\n    DebounceSeconds  int    `toml:\"debounce_seconds\"`\n    MinConfidence    string `toml:\"min_confidence\"`\n    MaxPromptBullets int    `toml:\"max_prompt_bullets\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Config File Location:**\n- Per-project: `<projectDir>/.cloche/config.toml`\n- Global daemon: `~/.config/cloche/config`\n\n---\n\n### WORKFLOW DSL\n\n#### DSL Parser\nFile: `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`\n\n```go\nfunc ParseAllForHost(input string) (map[string]*domain.Workflow, error)\n    // Parses host.cloche which can have multiple workflows\n    // Returns: map[workflowName]*domain.Workflow\n\nfunc ParseForContainer(input string) (*domain.Workflow, error)\n    // Parses container workflow file (*.cloche)\n    // Returns: single *domain.Workflow\n```\n\n#### Step Types\n```go\ntype StepType string\n\nconst (\n    StepTypeAgent    StepType = \"agent\"      // runs agent (Claude Code)\n    StepTypeScript   StepType = \"script\"     // runs shell command\n    StepTypeWorkflow StepType = \"workflow\"   // dispatches container run\n)\n```\n\n#### Result Markers\nSteps can use markers to override exit code behavior:\n- Format: `[CLOCHE_RESULT: <result>]` in output\n- Default: \"success\" on exit 0, \"fail\" on non-zero\n\n---\n\n### EXECUTION ENGINE\n\n#### Workflow Execution\nFile: `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`\n\n```go\ntype Engine struct {\n    executor       StepExecutor      // executes individual steps\n    status         StatusHandler     // receives progress events\n    maxSteps       int               // max steps per run (default: 1000)\n    defaultTimeout time.Duration     // default step timeout (default: 30m)\n}\n\ntype StepExecutor interface {\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error)\n}\n\ntype StatusHandler interface {\n    OnStepStart(run *domain.Run, step *domain.Step)\n    OnStepComplete(run *domain.Run, step *domain.Step, result string)\n    OnRunComplete(run *domain.Run)\n}\n\nfunc (e *Engine) Run(ctx context.Context, wf *domain.Workflow) (*domain.Run, error)\n    // Executes workflow graph starting from EntryStep\n    // Handles wiring, result routing, fanout/fanin\n    // Manages step timeouts\n```\n\n---\n\n### ACTIVE WORKERS AND RUNS TRACKING\n\n#### Run Persistence\nFile: `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n    ID          string             // unique run ID (generated)\n    State       RunState           // pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled\n    ActiveSteps []string           // steps currently executing\n    ParentRunID string             // for child runs (non-empty if launched by host workflow)\n    IsHost      bool               // true if this is a host workflow run\n    TaskID      string             // optional task ID this run is for\n}\n\nfunc TaskAggregateStatus(runs []*Run) RunState {\n    // Computes aggregate status for runs handling same task\n    // Active statuses (running, pending) outweigh terminal ones\n    // Returns state of most recent run if all terminal\n}\n```\n\n#### Run Store Interface\nFile: `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`\n\n```go\ntype RunStore interface {\n    CreateRun(ctx context.Context, run *Run) error\n    UpdateRun(ctx context.Context, run *Run) error\n    GetRun(ctx context.Context, runID string) (*Run, error)\n    ListRuns(ctx context.Context) ([]*Run, error)\n    ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*Run, error)\n    ListRunsByTask(ctx context.Context, taskID string) ([]*Run, error)\n    FailStaleRuns(ctx context.Context) (int, error)\n}\n```\n\n#### Active Run Tracking in Loop\nFile: `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` (lines 485-498)\n\n```go\nfunc (l *Loop) countActiveHostRuns() int {\n    runs, err := l.store.ListRunsByProject(ctx, l.config.ProjectDir, time.Time{})\n    count := 0\n    for _, r := range runs {\n        if r.IsHost && (r.State == domain.RunStatePending || r.State == domain.RunStateRunning) {\n            count++\n        }\n    }\n    return count\n}\n\n// Loop uses this to enforce MaxConcurrent limit:\n// - Counts active host runs at start of each iteration\n// - Only launches new runs if active < MaxConcurrent\n// - Waits for a run to complete before filling slot\n```\n\n---\n\n### KEY FILES SUMMARY\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche` | Host workflow definitions (list-tasks, main, finalize) |\n| `/workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche` | Container workflow definition |\n| `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/*.sh` | Host-side scripts for task lifecycle |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | Run state machine and execution tracking |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` | Workflow structure, steps, wiring |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/task.go` | Task types and task assigner interface |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` | Orchestration loop (three-phase or legacy) |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` | Host workflow step executor |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` | Host workflow runner, RunListTasksWorkflow |\n| `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` | Workflow execution engine |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | gRPC service, EnableLoop, GetProjectInfo, GetLoopTasks |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | Web dashboard handlers |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` | Project view HTML with task table |\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloche/project.go` | Project info CLI command |\n| `/workspace/internal/config/config.go` | Configuration loading (project and daemon) |\n\n---\n\n### WORKFLOW EXECUTION FLOW\n\n#### Container Workflow (develop.cloche)\n```\n1. User: cloche run develop --prompt \"...\"\n2. CLI: Sends RunWorkflow(workflow=\"develop\", projectDir=cwd)\n3. Daemon: Creates run, pulls/starts container, mounts project\n4. Container Agent: Parses workflow, walks graph, executes steps\n5. Steps: \n   - implement (agent step)\n   - test (script step)\n   - fix (agent step, with retry up to max_attempts)\n   - update-docs (agent step)\n6. Result: Commits to new branch cloche/{runID}\n7. Artifact: Branch contains all changes from workflow execution\n```\n\n#### Host Workflow Three-Phase (host.cloche)\n```\nPhase 1: list-tasks\n  cloche loop start\n  ├─ Runs list-tasks workflow\n  ├─ Execute: ready-tasks.sh → bd list\n  └─ Result: []Task (open tasks)\n\nPhase 2: main (for each open task, up to MaxConcurrent)\n  ├─ CLOCHE_TASK_ID=<task-id> set by daemon\n  ├─ claim-task.sh → bd update (set in_progress)\n  ├─ prepare-prompt.sh → bd show (fetch task details)\n  ├─ develop (dispatch container run, wait for result)\n  ├─ merge-to-main.sh (rebase branch onto main)\n  └─ cleanup-run.sh (remove worktree)\n  \n  Container Run Executes:\n    └─ develop workflow\n       ├─ implement (Claude Code)\n       ├─ test (bash: go test)\n       ├─ fix (Claude Code, retry on failure)\n       └─ update-docs (Claude Code)\n       \n  Result: cloche/{runID} branch merged to main\n\nPhase 3: finalize (after each main completes)\n  ├─ CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID=<child-run-id>\n  ├─ CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME=<succeeded|failed>\n  └─ close-task.sh → bd close (if succeeded)\n```\n\n---\n\n### TASK PIPELINE STATE\n\nThe orchestration loop maintains task state via three mechanisms:\n\n1. **lastTasks**: Most recently fetched tasks from list-tasks\n2. **dedup**: Task ID → assignment time (prevents rapid reassignment for DedupTimeout)\n3. **taskRuns**: Task ID → (RunID, AssignedAt) for tracking which run handled each task\n\n**GetTaskSnapshot()** combines these into TaskStateEntry for web dashboard:\n- Task details (ID, title, status, description, metadata)\n- Assigned: bool (true if within dedup window)\n- AssignedAt: time (when deduped or run started)\n- RunID: string (non-empty if main has completed for this task)\n\n---\n\nThis comprehensive exploration captures the full architecture of Cloche's task/bead system, project view implementation, and workflow execution mechanisms. All the key interfaces, data structures, and orchestration patterns are documented with file paths and line numbers for reference."}],"totalDurationMs":160476,"totalTokens":85708,"totalToolUseCount":59,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":166,"cache_read_input_tokens":78267,"output_tokens":7275,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":166},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
